---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Keep Android Open — arcbase"
  description="Android's open-source future is under threat. Learn what's happening, why it matters, and what you can do to help the #KeepAndroidOpen movement."
  keywords="keepandroidopen, android open source, AOSP, F-Droid, developer freedom, Google android policy, android walled garden"
  activePage="android"
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="kao-hero">
    <!---     <div class="kao-hero-bg" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="kao-orb kao-orb-1"></div>
      <div class="kao-orb kao-orb-2"></div>
      <div class="kao-orb kao-orb-3"></div>
    </div> --->
    <div class="kao-hero-content fade-up">
      <h1 class="kao-hero-title">
        Keep Android <span class="kao-struck-text">Open</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="kao-hero-sub">
        Google is quietly dismantling the open-source foundation of Android.
        Billions of users and millions of developers are at risk of losing the
        freedom to choose what runs on their own devices.
      </p>
      <div class="kao-hero-actions">
        <a
          href="https://www.keepandroidopen.com/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="btn-primary"
        >
          Sign the Open Letter ↗
        </a>
        <a href="#what-is-happening" class="btn-outline"
          >Learn what's happening</a
        >
      </div>
      <div class="kao-stats">
        <div class="kao-stat">
          <span class="kao-stat-num">3B+</span>
          <span class="kao-stat-label">Android users affected</span>
        </div>
        <div class="kao-stat-divider"></div>
        <div class="kao-stat">
          <span class="kao-stat-num">∞</span>
          <span class="kao-stat-label">FOSS apps at risk</span>
        </div>
        <div class="kao-stat-divider"></div>
        <div class="kao-stat">
          <span class="kao-stat-num">1</span>
          <span class="kao-stat-label">gatekeeper deciding it all</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT IS HAPPENING -->
  <section class="kao-section" id="what-is-happening">
    <div class="kao-container">
      <div class="kao-section-label">The Problem</div>
      <h2 class="kao-section-title">What is happening to Android?</h2>
      <p class="kao-section-intro">
        Android was built on a promise: an open platform where anyone could
        build, distribute, and run software without asking permission. Google is
        breaking that promise — and doing it piece by piece.
      </p>

      <div class="kao-cards">
        <div class="kao-card kao-card-red fade-up">
          <div class="kao-card-icon">
            <svg
              width="28"
              height="28"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.75"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              aria-hidden="true"
              ><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" ry="2"
              ></rect><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"></path></svg
            >
          </div>
          <h3>Mandatory Developer Registration</h3>
          <p>
            Google now requires <em>all</em> Android app developers — including independent,
            hobbyist, and FOSS developers — to register centrally with Google using
            government-issued ID and pay a fee, even if they never use the Play Store.
            Non-registered apps will not run on "certified" devices.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="kao-card kao-card-orange fade-up">
          <div class="kao-card-icon">
            <svg
              width="28"
              height="28"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.75"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              aria-hidden="true"
              ><line x1="3" y1="22" x2="21" y2="22"></line><line
                x1="6"
                y1="18"
                x2="6"
                y2="11"></line><line x1="10" y1="18" x2="10" y2="11"
              ></line><line x1="14" y1="18" x2="14" y2="11"></line><line
                x1="18"
                y1="18"
                x2="18"
                y2="11"></line><polygon points="12 2 2 7 22 7"></polygon></svg
            >
          </div>
          <h3>FOSS Ecosystems Under Threat</h3>
          <p>
            Projects like <strong>F-Droid</strong> — which provide a privacy-respecting,
            Google-free alternative app store — are directly threatened. Student developers,
            privacy advocates, and open-source maintainers who cannot or will not
            comply face being locked out of the platform entirely.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="kao-card kao-card-yellow fade-up">
          <div class="kao-card-icon">
            <svg
              width="28"
              height="28"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.75"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              aria-hidden="true"
              ><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2" ry="2"
              ></rect><line x1="8" y1="21" x2="16" y2="21"></line><line
                x1="12"
                y1="17"
                x2="12"
                y2="21"></line></svg
            >
          </div>
          <h3>A Walled Garden in the Making</h3>
          <p>
            These policies are transforming Android into an iOS-style walled
            garden where Google is the sole arbiter of what software users can
            install. Combined with reduced AOSP update frequency and
            closed-source creep into core system components, the open Android of
            old is disappearing fast.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="kao-card kao-card-purple fade-up">
          <div class="kao-card-icon">
            <svg
              width="28"
              height="28"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.75"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              aria-hidden="true"
              ><polyline points="23 18 13.5 8.5 8.5 13.5 1 6"
              ></polyline><polyline points="17 18 23 18 23 12"></polyline></svg
            >
          </div>
          <h3>Slower AOSP, Wider Gaps</h3>
          <p>
            Google shifted AOSP releases from quarterly to twice-yearly. This
            widens the gap between Google's internal development and the
            open-source community, making it harder for custom ROM developers
            and independent maintainers to keep pace — effectively starving the
            open ecosystem.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHY IT MATTERS -->
  <section class="kao-section kao-section-alt">
    <div class="kao-container">
      <div class="kao-section-label">Why It Matters</div>
      <h2 class="kao-section-title">
        This affects everyone — not just developers
      </h2>

      <div class="kao-two-col">
        <div class="kao-prose fade-up">
          <p>
            You might think this is only a developer problem. It isn't. Every
            person who uses an Android device is affected when the platform that
            powers their phone becomes a controlled, permission-gated
            environment.
          </p>
          <p>
            Open Android has always meant <strong>user choice</strong>: the
            freedom to install apps from any source, to run custom firmware, to
            use a device you legally own however you choose. When developers
            need Google's blessing to distribute software, that freedom is gone
            — and your device effectively becomes Google's property.
          </p>
          <p>
            The open-source ecosystem also underpins the security and privacy
            tools <em>millions</em> rely on daily: ad blockers, VPNs, encrypted messengers,
            parental controls, accessibility tools. Many of these exist outside the
            Play Store precisely because Google would not allow them. Under the new
            regime, they disappear.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="kao-impact-list fade-up">
          <div class="kao-impact-item">
            <span class="kao-impact-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg
                width="22"
                height="22"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="1.75"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                ><path d="M20 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H8a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"
                ></path><circle cx="12" cy="7" r="4"></circle></svg
              >
            </span>
            <div>
              <strong>Regular users</strong>
              <p>
                Lose the ability to install apps outside of Google's approved
                marketplace.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="kao-impact-item">
            <span class="kao-impact-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg
                width="22"
                height="22"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="1.75"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                ><polyline points="16 18 22 12 16 6"></polyline><polyline
                  points="8 6 2 12 8 18"></polyline></svg
              >
            </span>
            <div>
              <strong>Indie & FOSS developers</strong>
              <p>
                Face mandatory registration, fees, and identity disclosure just
                to ship code.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="kao-impact-item">
            <span class="kao-impact-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg
                width="22"
                height="22"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="1.75"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                ><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            <div>
              <strong>Privacy-focused tools</strong>
              <p>
                Many cannot meet Play Store policies — they will vanish from
                certified devices.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="kao-impact-item">
            <span class="kao-impact-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg
                width="22"
                height="22"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="1.75"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                ><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><line
                  x1="2"
                  y1="12"
                  x2="22"
                  y2="12"></line><path
                  d="M12 2a15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4-10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4-10z"
                ></path></svg
              >
            </span>
            <div>
              <strong>Global digital sovereignty</strong>
              <p>
                Nations and communities building on Android as a free platform
                lose that foundation.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT YOU CAN DO -->
  <section class="kao-section" id="take-action">
    <div class="kao-container">
      <div class="kao-section-label">Take Action</div>
      <h2 class="kao-section-title">What you can do right now</h2>
      <p class="kao-section-intro">
        You don't need to be a developer to make a difference. Every voice,
        every share, and every message to a lawmaker counts.
      </p>

      <div class="kao-actions-grid">
        <div class="kao-action-card fade-up">
          <div class="kao-action-number">01</div>
          <h3>Sign the Open Letter</h3>
          <p>
            The #KeepAndroidOpen coalition has drafted an open letter to Google
            and regulators demanding they reverse these policies. Add your name
            alongside thousands of developers and users.
          </p>
          <a
            href="https://www.keepandroidopen.com/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="kao-action-link">Sign now ↗</a
          >
        </div>

        <div class="kao-action-card fade-up">
          <div class="kao-action-number">02</div>
          <h3>Contact Your Lawmakers</h3>
          <p>
            Especially if you're in the EU, US, or UK — regulators are actively
            scrutinizing big tech platform control. Write to your representative
            and tell them you want open platforms protected by law.
          </p>
          <a
            href="https://www.keepandroidopen.com/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="kao-action-link">Find your rep ↗</a
          >
        </div>

        <div class="kao-action-card fade-up">
          <div class="kao-action-number">03</div>
          <h3>Spread the Word</h3>
          <p>
            Share <strong>#KeepAndroidOpen</strong> on social media. Most people have
            no idea this is happening. The more noise we make, the harder it is for
            Google to quietly close the platform.
          </p>
          <a
            href="https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Android%27s%20open-source%20future%20is%20under%20threat.%20Join%20me%20in%20supporting%20%23KeepAndroidOpen%20%E2%86%92%20https%3A%2F%2Fwww.keepandroidopen.com"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="kao-action-link">Share on X ↗</a
          >
        </div>

        <div class="kao-action-card fade-up">
          <div class="kao-action-number">04</div>
          <h3>Support F-Droid &amp; Alternatives</h3>
          <p>
            Use and donate to F-Droid and other open-source app ecosystems.
            Showing there is demand for open distribution channels strengthens
            the argument for keeping Android free.
          </p>
          <a
            href="https://f-droid.org/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="kao-action-link">Visit F-Droid ↗</a
          >
        </div>

        <div class="kao-action-card fade-up">
          <div class="kao-action-number">05</div>
          <h3>Don't Register Under Protest</h3>
          <p>
            If you're a developer, the coalition urges you not to participate in
            Google's mandatory registration program and to continue distributing
            your software through independent channels.
          </p>
          <a
            href="https://www.keepandroidopen.com/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="kao-action-link">Read the guidance ↗</a
          >
        </div>

        <div class="kao-action-card fade-up">
          <div class="kao-action-number">06</div>
          <h3>Stay Informed</h3>
          <p>
            Follow the official campaign hub for the latest news, action items,
            and resources. This situation is evolving — staying informed means
            you can respond when it matters most.
          </p>
          <a
            href="https://www.keepandroidopen.com/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="kao-action-link">keepandroidopen.com ↗</a
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ARCBASE STANCE -->
  <section class="kao-section kao-section-stance">
    <div class="kao-container">
      <div class="kao-stance-card fade-up">
        <div class="kao-stance-icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg
            width="40"
            height="40"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            ><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"></path></svg
          >
        </div>
        <div class="kao-stance-content">
          <h2>Arcbase stands with the open-source community</h2>
          <p>
            At Arcbase, we believe that the future of computing depends on open
            platforms and free software. Android's open foundation has enabled
            an entire generation of developers, privacy tools, and alternative
            ecosystems to thrive. We refuse to stand by while that foundation is
            eroded.
          </p>
          <p>
            We are proud to support the <strong>#KeepAndroidOpen</strong> movement
            and encourage everyone in our community to do the same. Open source is
            not just a development model — it's a statement about who gets to decide
            what technology does.
          </p>
          <a
            href="https://www.keepandroidopen.com/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="btn-primary"
          >
            Join the movement ↗
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="kao-section" id="faq">
    <div class="kao-container">
      <div class="kao-section-label">Email Templates</div>
      <div class="kao-faq">
        <details class="kao-faq-item">
          <summary class="kao-faq-summary">
            <span>DMA Team Email Template</span>
            <div class="kao-faq-icon">
              <svg
                width="18"
                height="18"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2.5"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                aria-hidden="true"
                ><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg
              >
            </div>
          </summary>
          <div class="kao-faq-body">
            <div class="email-template">
              <div class="email-header">
                <div class="email-field">
                  <span class="email-label">To</span>
                  <span class="email-value">EC-DMA@ec.europa.eu</span>
                </div>
                <div class="email-field">
                  <span class="email-label">CC</span>
                  <span class="email-value email-placeholder"
                    >your-email@example.com</span
                  >
                </div>
                <div class="email-field">
                  <span class="email-label">Subject</span>
                  <span class="email-value"
                    >DMA Complaint: Google Android Developer Verification
                    Program</span
                  >
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="email-body">
                <p>Dear Antitrust Division,</p>
                <p>
                  Dear DMA Team, I am writing to formally raise concerns about
                  Google's "Android Developer Verification" program, announced
                  August 2025 and scheduled for September 2026.
                </p>
                <p>
                  This program requires all developers to register with Google,
                  pay fees, submit government identification, and surrender
                  signing keys before their apps can be installed on Android
                  devices — including via sideloading. This effectively
                  eliminates the ability to freely install software on Android
                  devices, which is a core functionality that consumers relied
                  upon when purchasing these devices. It constitutes a
                  gatekeeper leveraging its dominant position to restrict
                  competition and consumer choice — precisely what the Digital
                  Markets Act was designed to prevent. I urge you to investigate
                  this program under Articles 5 and 6 of the DMA and take
                  enforcement action before the September 2026 deadline. Thank
                  you for your attention. Best regards
                </p>
                <p>Thank you for your time.</p>
                <p>Best regards</p>
              </div>
              <div class="email-actions">
                <button class="email-copy-btn" id="copyDmaEmail" type="button">
                  <svg
                    width="14"
                    height="14"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    fill="none"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    stroke-width="2.5"
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                    ><rect x="9" y="9" width="13" height="13" rx="2" ry="2"
                    ></rect><path
                      d="M5 15H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h9a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v1"
                    ></path></svg
                  >
                  Copy email body
                </button>
                <a
                  href="mailto:COMP-GREFFE-ANTITRUST@ec.europa.eu?subject=Antitrust%20Complaint%3A%20Google%20Android%20Developer%20Verification%20Program"
                  class="email-open-btn"
                >
                  <svg
                    width="14"
                    height="14"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    fill="none"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    stroke-width="2.5"
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                    ><path
                      d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"
                    ></path><polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"></polyline></svg
                  >
                  Open in mail app
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="kao-faq-item">
          <summary class="kao-faq-summary">
            <span>Antitrust Division Email Template</span>
            <div class="kao-faq-icon">
              <svg
                width="18"
                height="18"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2.5"
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                aria-hidden="true"
                ><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg
              >
            </div>
          </summary>
          <div class="kao-faq-body">
            <div class="email-template">
              <div class="email-header">
                <div class="email-field">
                  <span class="email-label">To</span>
                  <span class="email-value"
                    >COMP-GREFFE-ANTITRUST@ec.europa.eu</span
                  >
                </div>
                <div class="email-field">
                  <span class="email-label">CC</span>
                  <span class="email-value email-placeholder"
                    >your-email@example.com</span
                  >
                </div>
                <div class="email-field">
                  <span class="email-label">Subject</span>
                  <span class="email-value"
                    >Antitrust Complaint: Google Android Developer Verification
                    Program</span
                  >
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="email-body">
                <p>Dear Antitrust Division,</p>
                <p>
                  I am writing to raise a formal antitrust concern regarding
                  Google's "Android Developer Verification" program, set to take
                  effect September 2026.
                </p>
                <p>
                  This program will require all app developers to register with
                  Google, pay fees, and submit government identification before
                  their apps can be installed on any Android device — even
                  outside the Play Store.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Google controls approximately 75% of the global mobile OS
                  market. Using this dominance to impose mandatory registration
                  and fees on all software distribution — including channels
                  that bypass Google's own store — constitutes an abuse of
                  dominant market position and erects barriers to entry for
                  independent developers.
                </p>
                <p>
                  This eliminates the last remaining open major mobile platform
                  and removes meaningful competition in app distribution.
                </p>
                <p>
                  I urge the Commission to investigate this under Articles 101
                  and 102 TFEU.
                </p>
                <p>Thank you.</p>
                <p>Best regards</p>
              </div>
              <div class="email-actions">
                <button
                  class="email-copy-btn"
                  id="copyAntitrustEmail"
                  type="button"
                >
                  <svg
                    width="14"
                    height="14"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    fill="none"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    stroke-width="2.5"
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                    ><rect x="9" y="9" width="13" height="13" rx="2" ry="2"
                    ></rect><path
                      d="M5 15H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h9a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v1"
                    ></path></svg
                  >
                  Copy email body
                </button>
                <a
                  href="mailto:COMP-GREFFE-ANTITRUST@ec.europa.eu?subject=Antitrust%20Complaint%3A%20Google%20Android%20Developer%20Verification%20Program"
                  class="email-open-btn"
                >
                  <svg
                    width="14"
                    height="14"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    fill="none"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    stroke-width="2.5"
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    aria-hidden="true"
                    ><path
                      d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"
                    ></path><polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"></polyline></svg
                  >
                  Open in mail app
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* ===== KAO PAGE STYLES ===== */

  /* FAQ */
  .kao-faq {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .kao-faq-item {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 14px;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition:
      border-color 0.25s,
      box-shadow 0.25s;
  }

  .kao-faq-item:hover {
    border-color: rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.4);
